description:
“I take all these changes and try to embrace it. This is what it is now, let’s get the best out of this. … If you try to stay in the past in the music business, you’re in trouble.”

Lee Ritenour is one of the most prolific and renowned artists in jazz. The legendary guitarist has charted over 30 contemporary jazz hits, has been awarded a Grammy, and has played with the crème de la crème of the music scene. We caught up with Lee Ritenour for this #fhtz interview to talk about how he adapted to technological and social changes that disrupted the music business and were offered great insights and opinions.

Produced by Simon Kurt & Sebastiano Mereu | Videography by Digitale Massarbeit
